    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How often should I check my BMI?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>For most adults, checking your BMI once every three to six months is sufficient unless you are actively trying to lose or gain weight. If you are on a weight management program, monthly BMI tracking can help you monitor progress, though daily weight fluctuations of 2 to 4 pounds are normal due to water retention, food intake, and other factors. Rather than fixating on a single BMI number, focus on the trend over time. It is also more useful to track BMI alongside other metrics like waist circumference, body fat percentage, blood pressure, and blood sugar levels for a comprehensive health picture.</p></div>
    </details>

